title: ICE when trait alias with projection predicate is used in trait object types

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(trait_alias)] trait C { type Assoc; } trait D {} trait Alias = D where usize: C; fn foo(_: &dyn Alias<()>) {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.69.0-nightly (5243ea5c2 2023-02-20) binary: rustc commit-hash: 5243ea5c29b136137c36bd773e5baa663790e097 commit-date: 2023-02-20 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.69.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.7 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)` left: `usize`, right: `FreshTy(0)`', compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/astconv/mod.rs:1571:17 ```
